This article is a presidential memorandum issued by Barack Obama on May 31, 2011. The memorandum delegates the authority to appoint commissioned officers of the Ready Reserve Corps of the Public Health Service to a specific individual. Commissions issued under this authority are limited to a term of 6 months, and officers appointed through this delegation cannot serve in the Ready Reserve Corps for longer than 6 months unless appointed by the President or to the Regular Corps with Senate approval. The memorandum also states that this authority cannot be further delegated and directs the recipient to publish the memorandum in the Federal Register.